introduction.p:
The Stirling number of second kind S(n,k) is the number of partitions of the set [n] into exactly k blocks. (A block is a nonempty set.)
Here are the first rows of the Stirling triangle:
\begin{array}{lcccccccccccc} n&S(n,k)\\ \hline \\ 0 && & &&&& 1 \\ 1 && &&&& 0 && 1 \\ 2 && &&& 0 && 1 && 1 \\ 3 && && 0 && 1 && 3 && 1 \\ 4 &&& 0 && 1 && 7 && 6 && 1 \\ 5 && 0 && 1 && 15 && 25 && 10 && 1\\ \end{array}
